19:26.791 --> 19:29.458
-Oh. Oh, oh. Be careful, man.
-Yeah?

19:30.291 --> 19:32.416
I'll be careful. Later.

19:32.958 --> 19:34.083
Where's he going?

19:34.958 --> 19:37.041
[Paul]  He got something
to take care of, man.

19:47.291 --> 19:48.833
[footsteps approaching]

19:56.875 --> 19:57.875
Tiên...

20:00.041 --> 20:01.625
you have hardly changed.

20:01.708 --> 20:07.291
We both know that's not true.
But thank you for being so kind.

20:11.958 --> 20:13.833
You look like
you've done well for yourself.

20:14.416 --> 20:15.833
We find a way.

20:17.250 --> 20:21.541
-Yes, we do. When we can.
-Yes.

20:22.250 --> 20:24.166
[in Vietnamese]

20:26.291 --> 20:27.500
[Otis chuckles]

20:28.875 --> 20:30.958
[in English] The gold is belong
to Vietnamese government.

20:31.916 --> 20:35.166
Monsieur Desroche converts the gold
into cash.

20:36.125 --> 20:40.375
He's the only person that I know
who can handle a transaction of this size.

20:42.333 --> 20:45.083
-Have you dealt with him before?
-Yes.

20:46.083 --> 20:48.958
He's expensive. 20%.

20:50.083 --> 20:52.208
-[sighs]
-And I will need 10%.

20:52.291 --> 20:54.625
And there's no other way to move this?

20:55.458 --> 20:56.291
[door opens]

20:56.375 --> 20:59.166
-International export is my business.
-[door closes]

20:59.250 --> 21:01.791
-It's why you call me.
-Yeah.

21:02.666 --> 21:04.375
[woman in Vietnamese]

21:13.041 --> 21:16.250
[in English] This is my daughter, Michon.

21:18.583 --> 21:23.375
And this is my old friend Otis.
From American War.

21:24.250 --> 21:26.375
-[Otis whispers] It's, uh...
-Hello, Otis.

21:28.875 --> 21:30.375
It's very nice to meet you.

21:31.083 --> 21:32.375
[in Vietnamese]

21:33.000 --> 21:34.333
[in English] Thanks, my dear.

21:53.541 --> 21:54.541
[sighs]

22:13.916 --> 22:14.875
Is, uh...

22:20.166 --> 22:25.208
Is, uh... Is that our daughter? Our...

22:26.250 --> 22:28.333
Yes, she is.

22:31.166 --> 22:34.541
She was a bastard child of the enemy.

22:36.625 --> 22:38.208
I was a whore.

22:38.791 --> 22:42.541
Her father was a  moi,  the nigger.

22:45.333 --> 22:47.916
The white GI taught us that word.

22:48.833 --> 22:50.458
Everyone want us out.

22:51.583 --> 22:55.500
We was too dirty to even clean the toilet.

22:57.791 --> 23:01.500
They call our beautiful Michon
the cockroach.

23:07.208 --> 23:09.166
-Mmm?
-No.

23:19.458 --> 23:20.750
Good night, Tiên.

23:20.833 --> 23:22.416
Good night, Otis.

23:27.708 --> 23:29.291
[Michon in Vietnamese]

24:12.916 --> 24:14.375
[bell tolling]

24:24.125 --> 24:27.291
[in English] May I ask, how did they
end up in your possession?

24:27.375 --> 24:29.750
You ask a lotta goddamn questions,
wringer.

24:32.166 --> 24:36.333
Monsieur, maybe they're from a bank
you just knocked off in Manila.

24:36.416 --> 24:39.125
Or maybe the authorities
are looking for them.

24:39.208 --> 24:41.125
I don't need that kind of shit.

24:41.208 --> 24:43.583
We ain't no international criminals,
you dig?

24:43.666 --> 24:47.375
In my line of work,
I have to be very careful,

24:47.458 --> 24:51.458
and that means knowing exactly
who I am in business with.

24:51.541 --> 24:53.958
This cat getting on
my last goddamn nerve, man.

24:54.541 --> 24:57.208
Gentlemen, I believe
our business is finished.

24:57.291 --> 24:58.458
[Paul] Hey, wait a minute.

24:59.250 --> 25:02.083
Do me a favor. Sit down, please?
Just give us that respect.

25:04.000 --> 25:06.041
Where were Frenchies in World War II?

25:07.875 --> 25:10.083
Hitler had y'all by the snails.

25:11.083 --> 25:14.166
The goddamn US of A saved your asses.

25:14.250 --> 25:16.958
If it wasn't for good ol' Uncle Sam,
all of yous,

25:17.041 --> 25:20.750
y'all be speaking the  deutsche
eating bratwurst,

25:20.833 --> 25:26.541
schnitzels and sauerkraut instead
of croissants, snails and escargot.

25:26.625 --> 25:27.791
Come on, Blood. Let it go.

25:27.875 --> 25:29.458
-No, man, no.
-Just let it go!

25:29.541 --> 25:32.166
No, fuck that. I ain't done.

25:34.750 --> 25:37.500
This motherfucker can't tell me shit.

25:38.208 --> 25:40.750
My daddy, God rest his soul,

25:40.833 --> 25:45.041
landed in Normandy and killed  beaucoup
goose-stepping Nazis.

25:45.125 --> 25:49.541
Let me tell you something, them Nazis
weren't no punks neither. Not like you.

25:54.291 --> 25:56.875
-Yeah, okay, I'm done.
-You feel better?

25:56.958 --> 25:58.416
-Yeah.
-[Desroche] Well,

25:59.000 --> 26:04.666
I thank you for this ignorant American
one-sided version of World War II.

26:04.750 --> 26:08.583
Please understand. He taking big risk.

26:08.666 --> 26:09.916
And we ain't?

26:11.041 --> 26:15.250
DaRoach, we gotta trust you,
and you gotta trust us.

26:17.166 --> 26:18.416
[Otis] Mr. Desroche...

26:20.666 --> 26:24.375
Our platoon was ordered
to find a C-47 CIA plane

26:24.458 --> 26:28.166
that went down with a payroll
for the native people. The Lahu.

26:28.250 --> 26:30.958
Now, they didn't wanna be paid
in paper currency,

26:31.041 --> 26:35.250
so Uncle Sam was paying them in gold bars
for their help against the V.C.

26:35.958 --> 26:38.208
Well, we found the gold, and we...

26:38.291 --> 26:43.125
We bury it. For now.
They ask, we say the V.C. got it.

26:43.958 --> 26:46.791
Later on, we come back and collect.

26:46.875 --> 26:48.208
You mean rip it off.

26:48.291 --> 26:50.000
We ain't ripping off shit!

26:51.250 --> 26:53.416
Who feel like
they're ripping something off?

26:54.416 --> 26:57.708
We was the very first people
that died for this red, white and blue.

26:58.666 --> 26:59.833
Yeah, that's right.

27:00.708 --> 27:04.875
It was a soul brother, Crispus Attucks
at the motherfuckin' Boston Massacre.

27:05.708 --> 27:08.458
We been dying for this country
from the very get,

27:08.541 --> 27:11.041
hoping one day they'd give us
our rightful place.

27:11.125 --> 27:14.416
All they give us was a foot
up our black asses. Well, fuck that.

27:15.125 --> 27:20.000
I say the USA owe us. We built this bitch!

27:20.708 --> 27:22.208
So, what you sayin', Blood?

27:24.125 --> 27:27.750
I'm saying... we repossess this gold...

27:29.125 --> 27:32.666
like they about to come repossess
your cash yield convertible now.

27:32.750 --> 27:34.166
[all laughing]

27:36.666 --> 27:41.541
We repossess this gold for every single
black boot that never made it home.

27:42.333 --> 27:46.416
Every brother and sister stolen
from Mother Africa to Jamestown, Virginia

27:46.500 --> 27:48.791
way back in 1619.

27:51.083 --> 27:54.166
We give this gold to our people.

27:55.291 --> 27:58.375
You feel that? You feel it?

28:00.458 --> 28:03.125
-Now, let's bury our gold.
-[Paul] Reparations.

28:03.208 --> 28:05.208
-[glasses clink]
-[Norman] Bloods.

28:05.291 --> 28:06.708
-[gunshot echoes]
-[all]  Bloods.

28:06.791 --> 28:08.666
[distant gunfire]

28:11.000 --> 28:13.958
We went back a few weeks later,
but the area was napalmed,

28:14.041 --> 28:16.333
and we lost all of our landmarks.

28:16.416 --> 28:22.625
But recently, a mudslide has exposed
what might be the C-47's tail,

28:23.291 --> 28:26.375
and satellite pictures
have pinpointed the spot.

28:26.458 --> 28:29.958
Mmm. You're more informed
than your friend here.

28:30.041 --> 28:32.791
Sir, are you in or out?

28:47.500 --> 28:53.416
This is my last offer per kilo,
less my commission.

29:03.833 --> 29:04.875
Tiên said 20.

29:04.958 --> 29:09.208
One cannot carry millions of dollars
through US Customs.

29:09.708 --> 29:13.125
The extra two points will get you
a dummy corporation

29:13.208 --> 29:16.708
and a tax-free offshore account in Macau.

29:17.291 --> 29:21.083
You can then withdraw the funds
from any bank in the world.

29:21.166 --> 29:23.708
How do I know that you two
ain't a con artist team?

29:24.500 --> 29:28.250
As you said, you simply must trust us.

29:28.333 --> 29:32.458
Yeah, well, the extra 2%
comes outta her cut.

29:33.458 --> 29:34.291
That's right.

29:37.333 --> 29:39.500
-I'll cover it.
-Price of doing business.

29:40.416 --> 29:42.666
-So, we good?
-Yeah.

29:44.041 --> 29:45.958
-I'm good.
-Yeah, I'm good.

29:46.708 --> 29:52.125
And, sir, Uncle Sam did no better
than France in Vietnam.

29:53.958 --> 29:57.625
Gentlemen, I look forward
to seeing you again in a few days.

29:57.708 --> 29:59.125
If you will excuse me,

29:59.208 --> 30:02.083
I have a lot of things to do
for all of us.

30:02.916 --> 30:04.000
[in French]

30:05.750 --> 30:06.791
[in English] And, uh...

30:07.291 --> 30:08.416
vive la France.

30:10.041 --> 30:11.708
[in English] This motherfucker, man.

30:12.583 --> 30:13.750
-[door shuts]
-[water running]

30:14.458 --> 30:15.708
[softly] I don't take that.

30:16.791 --> 30:17.875
[water stops running]

30:26.291 --> 30:27.833
What the fuck are you doing here?

30:28.500 --> 30:29.625
I'm worried about you.

30:31.250 --> 30:32.083
Why?

30:33.500 --> 30:36.541
-Well, I found out you were coming here.
-And?

30:37.541 --> 30:39.250
And I came to check on you.

30:41.125 --> 30:44.541
You don't give a flying fuck
about me. [scoffs]

30:44.625 --> 30:47.583
I do. You been acting more crazy
than usual.

30:52.541 --> 30:53.500
Yeah, well...

30:56.041 --> 30:57.458
you consider me checked on.

30:59.208 --> 31:00.583
You're here for the gold.

31:01.375 --> 31:02.208
Don't lie.

31:03.458 --> 31:05.875
You're going after the gold.
I read Otis' emails.

31:07.125 --> 31:11.416
You gotta choose better passwords.
"1-2-3-4"?

31:12.375 --> 31:14.416
[laughs] Come on now, Dad.

31:15.083 --> 31:16.416
What do you want, David?

31:17.000 --> 31:19.583
-An equal share for helping you find it.
-Hell to the naw!

31:19.666 --> 31:23.166
The authorities find out about this,
y'all go back to the crib empty-handed.

31:23.916 --> 31:27.458
So, you just a lil' jive-ass
gangster now, huh?

31:27.541 --> 31:31.791
After everything you've put me through,
I'd say you getting a basement bargain.

31:33.000 --> 31:38.041
You ungrateful lil'...
lil' Black Studies teacher nigga.

31:40.333 --> 31:42.875
You want to tell your Bloods or should I?

31:49.958 --> 31:51.875
[Eddie] You sure know
how to raise 'em, don't you?

31:51.958 --> 31:55.541
What happens if we bum-rush your boy
and throw his ass off that balcony?

31:55.625 --> 31:57.500
Know I'm taking
a couple of you OGs with me.

31:57.583 --> 32:00.083
-Don't ever threaten my son, man.
-Or what?

32:00.166 --> 32:02.291
Or you will nab more trouble
than you know what to do with.

32:02.375 --> 32:03.625
-Oh, come on!
-Come on!

32:03.708 --> 32:05.166
Cool it, God damn it! Cool it!

32:06.958 --> 32:08.541
David, you are not getting a full share.

32:08.625 --> 32:11.041
-You and your daddy can split a share.
-You can forget that.

32:11.125 --> 32:12.333
You take it or leave it.

32:15.458 --> 32:16.625
[sighs]

32:17.833 --> 32:19.541
You see what you made me do, man?

32:20.458 --> 32:21.791
Let me tell you somethin'.

32:22.375 --> 32:25.625
You ain't been nothin'
but an anchor around my neck

32:25.708 --> 32:27.375
since the day you were born.

32:28.416 --> 32:33.083
Yeah, I said it, and I mean it, too.
Take this shit.

32:35.625 --> 32:36.708
God damn it.

32:37.708 --> 32:38.708
[door opens]

32:39.791 --> 32:41.041
[door slams]

32:41.125 --> 32:43.166
David, you're a buck private
in this outfit.

32:43.250 --> 32:47.833
You do what we say when we say it.
No questions asked. Understood?

32:49.375 --> 32:51.333
Overstood, Godfather.

33:00.875 --> 33:04.958
-I have bad feeling about this, Otis.
-I'm gonna be all right.

33:05.541 --> 33:10.833
Gold does strange things to people.
Even old friends. Be safe.

33:22.125 --> 33:24.083
All right. Yeah.

33:25.916 --> 33:27.750
I just hope I don't have to use it.

33:34.500 --> 33:36.208
I'll see you in a bit, all right?

33:38.250 --> 33:40.750
["Ride of the Valkyries" playing]

34:30.791 --> 34:31.916
[inaudible mutter]

35:23.875 --> 35:26.500
-[David] You just gonna stay there?
-Motherfucker, go around.

35:26.583 --> 35:27.875
[chuckling]

35:40.083 --> 35:42.000
-David.
-Yeah?

35:42.083 --> 35:43.625
Why did you come here?

35:46.958 --> 35:48.333
Well, he's my dad.

35:51.291 --> 35:53.041
Feels like my last chance with him.

35:56.333 --> 35:58.875
-He needs counseling.
-I know.

35:59.958 --> 36:02.208
-Talks to himself.
-[sighs]

36:05.291 --> 36:08.000
Your pops was never the same
after we lost Norman.

36:09.750 --> 36:10.750
[Otis] Hmm.

36:11.833 --> 36:15.458
-You know, he calls his name in his sleep.
-I can believe that.

36:17.791 --> 36:20.125
-Who was that guy?
-Norm?

36:21.958 --> 36:25.166
That brother was the best damn soldier
that ever lived.

36:28.708 --> 36:30.458
-[gun cocks]
-[bugs chirring loudly]

36:47.875 --> 36:50.083
[Otis]  Wasn't many brothers
who made squad leader.

36:51.166 --> 36:53.375
The man was using Bloods
for cannon fodder.

36:54.083 --> 36:56.916
White boys who stayed in college,
they'd dodge that shit.

36:58.000 --> 37:00.291
They put our poor black asses
on the front line,

37:00.375 --> 37:02.083
killing us off like flies.

37:04.750 --> 37:06.833
[soldiers speaking Vietnamese in distance]

37:06.916 --> 37:11.458
Stormin' earned his name,
was in all kind of firefights.

37:12.083 --> 37:13.916
Trained us in the way of the jungle.

37:14.000 --> 37:17.500
Made us believe
that we would get home, alive.

37:24.625 --> 37:26.625
[man 1 in Vietnamese]

37:34.375 --> 37:36.041
[soldiers exclaiming]

37:36.125 --> 37:38.250
[man 2 speaking]

37:38.333 --> 37:40.000
[man 1 speaking]

37:46.166 --> 37:48.333
[man 2 speaking]

37:48.416 --> 37:49.666
[man 1 speaking]

37:49.750 --> 37:52.791
[man 3 speaking]

37:53.291 --> 37:54.416
[soldiers scream]

37:55.083 --> 37:56.166
[in English] To your left!

37:56.250 --> 37:59.666
-[Paul] To your left!
-[Norman] To the left! Go, go!

38:07.166 --> 38:08.041
[Norman] Go!

38:08.250 --> 38:09.208
[grunts]

38:21.708 --> 38:23.208
-[Norman] Cease fire!
-[Eddie] Cease fire!

38:23.291 --> 38:25.000
-[Paul] Cease fire!
-Cease fire!

38:25.583 --> 38:27.458
-[Otis] Everybody all right?
-[Melvin] Yeah.

38:27.541 --> 38:29.250
-[Paul] Good right here.
-[Eddie] Good, good.

38:32.291 --> 38:33.750
War is about money.

38:36.250 --> 38:37.583
Money is about war.

38:38.333 --> 38:40.541
Every time I walk out my front door,

38:41.083 --> 38:43.833
I see cops patrolling my neighborhood
like it's some police state.

38:43.916 --> 38:47.291
I can feel just how much I ain't worth.

38:50.375 --> 38:52.750
-[slide projector clicks]
-[Otis]  Gave us something to believe in.

38:53.333 --> 38:55.375
A direction, a purpose.

38:56.541 --> 38:59.750
He taught us about black history
when it wasn't really popular back then.

39:01.041 --> 39:04.541
Schooled us about drinking that
anti-commie Kool-Aid they was selling.

39:05.333 --> 39:08.250
Yeah, he was our Malcolm and our Martin.

39:09.291 --> 39:11.916
Norm had a way of keeping us
from going off.

39:12.750 --> 39:14.000
He wasn't no Tom.

39:15.250 --> 39:18.166
He was a bad mother, shut your mouth.

39:18.250 --> 39:19.375
[chuckles]

39:20.166 --> 39:21.166
Like Ali.

39:27.291 --> 39:32.541
[woman over radio]  This is the voice
of Vietnam, broadcasting from Hanoi,

39:32.625 --> 39:37.041
capital of the Democratic Republic
of Vietnam.

39:41.333 --> 39:42.666
Black GI,

39:43.625 --> 39:49.583
in Memphis, Tennessee, a white man
assassinate Dr. Martin Luther King...

39:50.708 --> 39:53.875
who heroically opposed the cruel

39:53.958 --> 39:57.458
-racial discrimination in the USA.
-[single gunshot]

39:58.166 --> 40:02.791
Dr. King also opposed
the US war in Vietnam.

40:04.541 --> 40:10.291
Black GI, your government
sent 600,000 troops

40:10.375 --> 40:11.916
to crush the rebellion.

40:12.541 --> 40:19.500
Your soul sister and soul brothers
are enraged in over 122 cities.

40:20.125 --> 40:27.083
They kill them while you fight against us,
so far away from where you are needed.

40:29.250 --> 40:33.916
Black GI, the South Vietnamese people
are resolute

40:34.000 --> 40:37.041
against these fascist acts against Negroes

40:37.541 --> 40:40.250
who struggle for civil rights and freedom.

40:42.750 --> 40:47.916
Negroes are only 11% of the US population,

40:48.500 --> 40:52.208
but among troops here in Vietnam,
you are 32%.

40:54.625 --> 40:59.333
Black GI, is it fair to serve more
than the white Americans

40:59.416 --> 41:00.666
that sent you here?

41:01.166 --> 41:06.416
Nothing is more confuse
than to be ordered into a war to die

41:06.916 --> 41:12.041
or to be maimed for life without
the faintest idea of what's going on.

41:13.416 --> 41:15.791
I dedicate this next record

41:15.875 --> 41:19.625
to the soul brothers
of the 1st Infantry Divisions.

41:20.291 --> 41:24.916
Big Red One, 2nd Battalion,
136th Regiment.

41:25.708 --> 41:27.458
Have a good day, gentlemen.

41:31.416 --> 41:32.416
Be safe.

41:33.625 --> 41:36.708
-Goddamn bullshit.
-Got the wrong motherfucking enemy!

41:36.791 --> 41:39.125
Yeah, goddamn white man gone too far.

41:39.208 --> 41:42.500
-The Bible says an eye for an eye.
-And a tooth for a tooth.

41:42.583 --> 41:44.250
We need to kill some crackers.

41:44.333 --> 41:47.333
Our brothers and sisters
are burnin' shit down back home, Norm.

41:48.458 --> 41:51.541
I love you, man, but you're wrong.
Dead wrong.

41:51.625 --> 41:56.333
You're talking about Dr. King.
You're talking about a man of peace.

41:56.916 --> 41:58.791
And that's what got Dr. King killed.

41:59.291 --> 42:03.041
I'm as mad as everybody.
All us Bloods got a right to be, but...

42:05.208 --> 42:06.375
we Bloods.

42:07.875 --> 42:11.416
Won't let nobody use our rage against us.
We control our rage.

42:12.416 --> 42:16.041
Now, what y'all are trying to do right now
ain't changing shit.

42:17.458 --> 42:20.000
So, stand down. That's an order.

42:20.083 --> 42:22.166
Nah. Fuck an order, Norm!

42:25.666 --> 42:27.416
You're gonna have to kill me first.

42:29.958 --> 42:31.250
Blood on Blood.

43:29.333 --> 43:30.583
[screams]

43:31.791 --> 43:33.208
[all screaming]

43:36.583 --> 43:40.458
[Otis]  And let me tell you, out of all
of us, your pops was closest to him.

43:40.958 --> 43:43.083
Believed in Norman like a religion.

43:43.583 --> 43:46.166
I don't think he believed
in anything since.

43:47.916 --> 43:51.375
[Vinh] Floating market.
You brothers want anything?

43:51.458 --> 43:52.750
[Eddie] Is there some barbecue up in here?

43:52.833 --> 43:54.291
[Melvin] I might get a couple of things.

43:54.375 --> 43:55.958
[Vinh speaking Vietnamese]

43:57.666 --> 43:59.791
[Eddie in English] What's that?
You got bananas?

43:59.875 --> 44:02.125
[speaking Vietnamese]

44:02.208 --> 44:04.625
-Whoa!
-Hey, who wants a cold one?

44:04.708 --> 44:05.750
[overlapping chatter]

44:05.833 --> 44:07.791
-Six pack.
-[Paul] Bring 'em on up.

44:07.875 --> 44:09.250
Hey, don't let her get on.

44:11.125 --> 44:11.958
That's good.

44:12.041 --> 44:13.000
Hey!

44:13.416 --> 44:14.708
-Oranges?
-[Eddie] Get your beer here.

44:14.791 --> 44:16.208
-[Vinh] This is good.
-[Eddie] Here you go.

44:16.291 --> 44:19.833
You're gonna cut it open? No, I'm good.
So, how you eat it?

44:21.166 --> 44:22.208
It tastes like chicken.

44:22.291 --> 44:25.125
That probably don't taste like chicken.
That's race-related.

44:25.208 --> 44:27.875
[in Vietnamese]

44:29.916 --> 44:30.958
[David in English] Got any money?

44:31.041 --> 44:33.791
-[speaking Vietnamese]
-No, man. Not today.  Không.

44:33.875 --> 44:35.166
Không. Không.  No.

44:35.250 --> 44:36.416
[David] Let me get some bananas.

44:36.500 --> 44:38.375
-[Otis] I know, that's what I'm getting.
-[David] Bananas.

44:38.458 --> 44:39.583
[all laughing]

44:40.375 --> 44:42.333
-That's amazing.
-[David] You see this?

44:42.416 --> 44:44.583
No, and thank you. Yes, it is.
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

44:44.666 --> 44:45.583
[Paul] There you go.

44:46.041 --> 44:47.875
[David] That's great. No, thank you.
No, thanks.

44:47.958 --> 44:50.541
[in broken English]

44:50.625 --> 44:52.250
-Hello!
-[David] What's up with that?

44:52.333 --> 44:54.375
-Hey. [grunts]
-[seller speaking Vietnamese]

44:54.458 --> 44:56.125
No, not today. Not today.

44:56.208 --> 44:57.291
[in Vietnamese]

44:59.375 --> 45:02.666
[in English] No, I don't want it.
Nah. No, I--

45:02.750 --> 45:04.500
-Chicken.
-No, man. I...

45:04.583 --> 45:05.708
[chuckles] No, man. I...

45:07.041 --> 45:09.291
Okay, due respect. No.

45:09.875 --> 45:10.833
[in Vietnamese]

45:10.916 --> 45:12.583
[in English]
No. Okay, all due respect, no.

45:13.166 --> 45:14.708
Vinh, talk to your... Talk to this man.

45:15.083 --> 45:18.041
Come on, no means no
in any motherfucking language, right?

45:18.125 --> 45:20.541
Come on, man. Come talk to him, man.

45:21.500 --> 45:23.666
-[speaking Vietnamese]
-[Paul in English] No!

45:23.750 --> 45:25.291
-[Paul speaking Vietnamese]
-[exclaims]

45:25.375 --> 45:26.750
[in English] Vinh, come talk to him!

45:26.833 --> 45:31.666
No, man! Back up, okay.
Just back up. Back up, please.

45:31.750 --> 45:32.708
[Vinh in Vietnamese]

45:32.791 --> 45:35.750
Shut the fuck up.
I don't wanna hear that gook shit.

45:35.833 --> 45:37.750
[speaking Vietnamese]

45:38.583 --> 45:40.458
-[in English] You know what?
-[speaking Vietnamese]

45:40.541 --> 45:42.166
[in English] Fuck this place, man.

45:42.250 --> 45:43.875
-Backward-ass people.
-[speaking Vietnamese]

45:43.958 --> 45:46.375
-Hey! Get that fucking thing off of me!
-Hey, get him.

45:46.458 --> 45:48.875
-These backward-ass motherfuckers, man.
-Yeah. Let's go.

45:48.958 --> 45:52.291
-Shit! I don't know what the fuck he got!
-[Otis] Come on. Come on, man.

45:52.375 --> 45:54.583
-No, motherfucker!
-Let's go. Dad, come on.

45:54.666 --> 45:56.458
[Eddie] Man, it's just a goddamn chicken.

45:56.541 --> 45:58.291
[seller in Vietnamese]

45:58.375 --> 45:59.875
[in English]

45:59.958 --> 46:01.333
Huh? What?

46:02.375 --> 46:04.166
[overlapping shouts]

46:04.250 --> 46:06.416
You don't know nothing about me, man!
Fuck that!

46:06.500 --> 46:08.291
[in Vietnamese]

46:08.375 --> 46:09.666
[Paul] You don't know shit about me!

46:09.750 --> 46:12.541
I didn't kill your mother and father!
Fuck you!

46:12.625 --> 46:14.541
-[Vinh speaking Vietnamese]
-[Paul] You don't know me!

46:14.625 --> 46:15.583
[David] Let's go. Come on.

46:15.666 --> 46:17.666
You don't know what the fuck
you're talking about!

46:17.750 --> 46:20.250
-[Vinh speaking Vietnamese]
-[Paul] What the fuck you know about me?

46:20.875 --> 46:23.458
-[speaking English]
-Paul, relax!

46:23.541 --> 46:25.541
-Man, nah! He kept coming up on me!
-[speaking Vietnamese]

46:25.625 --> 46:27.625
-[Otis] I know.
-What the fuck?

46:27.708 --> 46:29.791
-[speaking Vietnamese]
-[Paul] What the fuck is going down?

46:29.875 --> 46:32.250
-I got you. I got you, brother.
-[seller speaking Vietnamese]

46:32.333 --> 46:33.500
Stop talking, and fuck you!

46:33.583 --> 46:35.208
-Get the boat moving!
-Move on, man!

46:35.291 --> 46:37.041
-I got you.
-Stop fucking talking!

46:37.125 --> 46:39.875
-Don't know shit about me.
-You killed my father and mother!

46:39.958 --> 46:41.041
What are you doing?

46:41.125 --> 46:42.916
He knows what "gook" means, man!

46:43.000 --> 46:44.541
I don't give a fuck about that!

46:44.625 --> 46:47.750
I don't give two fucks about that.
I tried to talk to the man.

46:47.833 --> 46:50.750
-[speaking Vietnamese]
-[Paul] Put the fucking camera down.

46:50.833 --> 46:53.833
You're just having a panic attack.
This shit happen to you all the time?

46:54.333 --> 46:56.333
-Yeah, he has PTSD.
-This happen all the time?

46:56.416 --> 46:57.583
-He gets triggered.
-Come on.

46:57.666 --> 46:59.625
[David] The guy off with his shit.
It be all right.

46:59.708 --> 47:02.541
Hey, David. What you know about it, huh?

47:02.625 --> 47:04.333
You don't know nothin' about this.

47:04.958 --> 47:08.041
-I don't have no fucking--
-Nightmares. You been having nightmares.

47:08.125 --> 47:09.875
-He does.
-I don't have no nightmares.

47:09.958 --> 47:11.250
-[David] You do.
-[Eddie] We all got PTSD.

47:11.333 --> 47:13.500
-[Paul] Come on and tell me. Look.
-Just breathe, come on.

47:13.583 --> 47:14.458
I see...

47:15.541 --> 47:16.750
-Come on.
-I...

47:16.833 --> 47:21.291
Come on, bud. Come on.
There you go. There you go.

47:22.125 --> 47:24.125
-Come on.
-I see ghosts, y'all. [voice breaks]

47:24.833 --> 47:25.958
I see...

47:28.208 --> 47:29.041
ghosts.

47:29.125 --> 47:31.041
Well, it happens to all of us, man!

47:31.125 --> 47:32.708
-You seen 'em, too?
-Yeah.

47:33.208 --> 47:35.541
Dead come to you at night? Huh?

47:36.666 --> 47:39.250
Stormin' Norm comes to me
damn near every night.

47:39.333 --> 47:42.083
Now, he talk to y'all like he talk to me?

47:42.166 --> 47:44.375
-[Otis] Brother, come on.
-I don't think so.

47:44.458 --> 47:46.083
Come on. Come on.

47:46.166 --> 47:47.958
-Take it easy, man.
-Go ahead, get it out.

47:48.041 --> 47:49.625
-Yeah.
-Get it out. Come on now.

47:50.208 --> 47:52.458
-Come on, bud.
-Think I'm a crazy fuck, don't you?

47:52.541 --> 47:53.625
No!

47:53.708 --> 47:55.000
-[Eddie] Come on, man.
-Smart niggas, huh?

47:55.083 --> 47:57.083
-[Otis] It ain't like that.
-Man, don't call me that.

47:57.166 --> 48:00.041
That's right. Y'all saditty niggas
don't like that word.

48:00.125 --> 48:02.916
You know what, man? Nigga. Nigga.

48:03.000 --> 48:07.791
Nigga. Nigga. Nigga! [chuckles]
A yellow nigga.

48:07.875 --> 48:08.791
-[Eddie] What?
-You feel me?

48:08.875 --> 48:11.750
Look, I'm tired of this bullshit!
Squash it!

48:12.916 --> 48:15.666
I'm with you. I'm with you.

48:18.416 --> 48:19.250
Fists up!

48:24.833 --> 48:27.875
Get in there, David. Get in there.
Put your fist up, David.

48:29.458 --> 48:30.291
Come on.

48:31.083 --> 48:35.041
You, too, Vinh. Go ahead! Fist up, man.

48:35.541 --> 48:36.583
Come on, Paul.

48:40.958 --> 48:45.000
-Bloods!
-Norm! Norm!

49:21.583 --> 49:23.083
-Get that out of my face.
-[Eddie laughs]

49:23.166 --> 49:24.000
Get that out of my face.

49:33.208 --> 49:35.208
[indistinct conversation in Vietnamese]

49:36.708 --> 49:38.500
[man in English] And I told him,
"Pick your poison,"

49:38.583 --> 49:40.833
and he told the waitress
to pick the poison.

49:41.500 --> 49:42.416
-Excuse me.
-Sorry.

49:43.291 --> 49:44.916
-[man] How's it going, boss?
-[David] How you doin'?

49:45.000 --> 49:46.333
[man] I'll be better at the bar.

49:53.125 --> 49:55.291
[David] Didn't think I'd meet
another American here.

49:59.666 --> 50:01.208
But I'm French. [chuckles]

50:01.291 --> 50:03.125
-Beg your pardon?
-I'm French.

50:04.125 --> 50:04.958
Sit.

50:07.375 --> 50:08.875
You're traveling alone?

50:09.583 --> 50:11.958
I'm here with a group of Vietnam vets.

50:13.291 --> 50:14.541
One is my father.

50:16.166 --> 50:18.125
Must be something powerful,

50:18.208 --> 50:20.666
coming back after all these years
with your father.

50:21.250 --> 50:22.875
-Yeah, it's powerful all right.
-Yeah.

50:24.166 --> 50:25.083
What is your name?

50:25.666 --> 50:30.375
Hedy. Like Hedy Lamarr. No?

50:30.458 --> 50:32.666
Old time Hollywood star.

50:33.875 --> 50:36.375
But, well, my last name is Bouvier, so...

50:37.833 --> 50:38.666
Cool.

50:39.375 --> 50:40.250
It's cool.

50:41.416 --> 50:44.708
-Uh, I'm David.
-Ah, David from the Bible.

50:45.250 --> 50:48.625
-Like David Ruffin from the Temptations.
-[Hedy chuckles]

50:49.375 --> 50:50.458
Motown.

50:52.166 --> 50:53.333
Yeah, you got it.

50:56.708 --> 50:59.166
Is there another place
to go at night around here?

50:59.250 --> 51:02.000
["Time Has Come Today"
by The Chambers Brothers playing]

51:08.000 --> 51:10.000
[indistinct chatter]

51:14.125 --> 51:17.083
Have you ever seen
so many scooters in your life? [chuckles]

51:20.208 --> 51:21.041
Thank you.

51:21.125 --> 51:22.000
[waitress in Vietnamese]

51:23.916 --> 51:24.958
So...

51:27.416 --> 51:28.791
what's their story?

51:29.375 --> 51:32.500
Well, Simon is my best friend.

51:33.708 --> 51:38.291
And Seppo and I use each other for sex
once in a blue moon.

51:39.291 --> 51:44.750
What do you, Simon and Sep... Seppo...
Seppo... what do you do?

51:44.833 --> 51:49.375
We locate old landmines,
and detonate bombs, too.

51:49.458 --> 51:50.500
Wow!

51:51.541 --> 51:53.166
-Wow, okay.
-"Wow, okay!" [laughs]

51:53.250 --> 51:55.458
Yeah, that's some gangster shit. For sure!

51:56.250 --> 52:01.000
How does one get involved in
the landmine disposal business? Pray tell.

52:01.833 --> 52:04.500
The Bouviers have a history in Vietnam.

52:06.083 --> 52:09.500
It's strange how a war never ends
for those involved.

52:09.583 --> 52:12.916
See, like, landmines planted years ago...

52:13.833 --> 52:17.166
and still harvesting death
all these years later.

52:17.583 --> 52:19.166
Back to your family history.

52:19.666 --> 52:25.000
My family made several fortunes
owning a rubber plantation,

52:25.875 --> 52:30.125
and then they bought up much more of
the rice market and made another fortune.

52:30.208 --> 52:31.750
See, the white gold.

52:33.541 --> 52:34.416
Hmm.

52:36.208 --> 52:37.791
Wonderful family business.

52:38.916 --> 52:42.666
But one exception, we exploited
the shit out of the Vietnamese people.

52:43.500 --> 52:45.625
So, that's the meaning behind the mines.

52:46.291 --> 52:49.041
So, what did the Bouvier family
think about what you do?

52:49.125 --> 52:50.375
[chuckles] What family?

52:53.708 --> 52:59.625
I'm the founder and the director of LAMB,
which I started three years ago.

52:59.708 --> 53:00.541
LAMB?

53:00.625 --> 53:04.583
Yeah, LAMB. Love Against Mines and Bombs.

53:08.083 --> 53:12.750
[laughs] No. I must look like
some Patty Hearst heiress

53:12.833 --> 53:17.541
who's cast herself
as a guilt-ridden bourgeoisie cliché.

53:18.041 --> 53:20.666
Hey, look,
I know all about bourgeoisie clichés.

53:21.500 --> 53:24.916
I'm a poverty-stricken fool
who loves teaching kids.

53:25.500 --> 53:28.291
However, my guilt trip
is a lot less dangerous than yours.

53:28.375 --> 53:29.833
-Yeah, less dangerous.
-Yeah.

53:29.916 --> 53:32.125
-[Hedy laughing]
-Unless you count school shootings.

53:33.375 --> 53:35.125
School shootings. No fun.

53:37.000 --> 53:39.833
You always been the solid one, always.

53:40.541 --> 53:44.875
Got a... wife who loves you.
Daughter who loves you.

53:45.625 --> 53:48.500
You got a son who loves you enough
for two daddies.

53:48.583 --> 53:50.416
I couldn't love David...

53:53.625 --> 53:54.500
back.

53:58.583 --> 54:02.250
You got back to the world,
you made that transition.

54:03.208 --> 54:07.083
Me, I'm all... fucked up inside.

54:08.083 --> 54:09.541
I'm broken, man.

54:15.583 --> 54:16.500
Broken.

54:18.666 --> 54:21.250
-[sobs] Fuck.
-Whoa, whoa, whoa.

54:24.166 --> 54:26.916
-Blood, we're all broken.
-Not like me, man.

54:28.000 --> 54:32.333
Norm and I were holding those gooks back
when the man bought it. I see him.

54:36.208 --> 54:37.541
I saw him die, man.

54:42.791 --> 54:43.791
[Paul clears throat]

54:43.875 --> 54:46.958
-So what? You're blaming yourself?
-You don't even know.

54:52.333 --> 54:56.041
Paul, when we get back to the world,
I'd like you to come with me to a meeting.

54:56.125 --> 55:00.000
I don't do that "sit in a circle,
whine about shit" group thing, man.

55:00.083 --> 55:03.041
I don't do it.
I never have and I never will.

55:03.125 --> 55:05.375
You got to talk to somebody.

55:05.458 --> 55:09.458
I talk to my brother Stormin' Norman
every single night.

55:12.625 --> 55:15.000
[in Vietnamese]

55:17.708 --> 55:20.041
-[in English] Yeah.
-Oh, oh, oh, drink, drink.

55:20.125 --> 55:21.791
[chattering indistinctly]

55:21.875 --> 55:24.000
[in Vietnamese]

55:28.333 --> 55:29.541
Whoa.

55:33.458 --> 55:36.375
[in English] Hey. Simon.

55:38.000 --> 55:40.708
-David.
-David. Okay. How's it going?

55:40.791 --> 55:41.625
I can't call it.

55:42.625 --> 55:45.208
Hey, that dude over there by the bar,
is he with you?

55:45.291 --> 55:47.333
-He's getting pretty shit-faced.
-Uh-huh. Brotherman.

55:47.416 --> 55:49.125
[Seppo in Finnish]

55:52.166 --> 55:54.125
[in English] It's been an emotional trip.

55:54.708 --> 55:56.250
[in English] It appears so.

55:56.625 --> 55:59.833
You Americans are just
incredibly uninformed.

56:01.666 --> 56:04.208
I guess you're too busy
watching reality TV,

56:04.833 --> 56:07.875
or electing a reality TV clown
for a president.

56:07.958 --> 56:08.875
Knew that was coming.

56:08.958 --> 56:12.500
Well, on behalf of all the black folks
in the USA,

56:12.583 --> 56:15.291
which are the only group
who didn't vote for the motherfucker,

56:15.375 --> 56:19.666
we plead innocent to all charges,
claims, accusations, allegations,

56:19.750 --> 56:23.208
and associations connected to the Klansman
in the Oval Office,

56:23.291 --> 56:24.416
so help me God.

56:24.500 --> 56:26.250
[in Vietnamese]

56:27.500 --> 56:30.708
The Bloods search
for the lost treasure of youth

56:30.791 --> 56:33.791
and the remains of the dearly departed
Norman Earl Holloway...

56:33.875 --> 56:38.416
-We're going.
-...KIA, December 7th, 1971.

56:39.375 --> 56:43.583
We're here to bring home
a fallen brother. A brother!

56:44.708 --> 56:50.166
A tomb is sacred, not to be looted
by rogues and vandals.

56:50.250 --> 56:54.375
There's gold in them hills!
Gold, goddamn it, gold!

56:56.041 --> 56:58.041
[dramatic instrumental music plays]

57:00.125 --> 57:02.583
[bugs chirring, birds twittering]

57:32.666 --> 57:34.208
[Melvin] Thanks for getting us
this far, Vinh.

57:34.291 --> 57:35.125
[Vinh] My pleasure.

57:35.208 --> 57:37.833
I gotta tell you, you put on
one hell of a tour.

57:37.916 --> 57:41.541
-[Otis] Sure do. Thanks Vinhi-vin.
-[Vinh] You're welcome.

57:42.250 --> 57:47.166
Nothing is more precious than independence
and liberty. Said by our uncle.

57:47.250 --> 57:49.916
-[Otis] What uncle?
-Uncle Ho Chi Minh.

57:50.000 --> 57:51.708
-Now he's your uncle?
-[chuckles]

57:51.791 --> 57:54.791
Actually, he's the father
of modern-day Vietnam.

57:54.875 --> 57:56.416
Like your George Washington.

57:56.500 --> 58:01.291
Oh, my dear misinformed,
misguided... Thank you.

58:01.958 --> 58:03.291
...Vietnamese brother.

58:04.000 --> 58:08.250
Our Uncle George owned 123 slaves.

58:09.083 --> 58:14.000
And as they say
in our colonists' second language, touché.

58:14.583 --> 58:18.375
[Paul] Get your arms out, man.
Get your arms out. And back, too.

58:19.458 --> 58:23.666
All right, get my arms and my back, man.
What's up? Arms and back!

58:23.750 --> 58:25.125
[David] There, I got you. I got you.

58:25.208 --> 58:27.625
Bloods, I can't believe
we back up in this bitch.

58:28.791 --> 58:31.458
I'll meet you at this rendezvous location
in a few days.

58:31.541 --> 58:33.541
-All right.
-If you're late or early, don't worry.

58:33.625 --> 58:34.583
I'll be there.

58:35.125 --> 58:36.583
I hope you find your friend.

58:41.541 --> 58:42.666
Bon voyage.

58:43.166 --> 58:45.666
[all in Vietnamese]

58:46.458 --> 58:47.958
[in English] Showtime. Showtime, baby.

58:50.708 --> 58:53.833
Bloods. I'm gonna teach you that.
Y'all ready?

58:53.916 --> 58:54.916
-Yeah, let's go.
-Yeah.

58:55.000 --> 58:55.916
You got the paperwork?

58:56.000 --> 58:57.916
[Otis] You can see I got
the paperwork with me.

58:58.000 --> 59:00.083
[Melvin] Is that a MAGA hat? God damn!

59:00.166 --> 59:02.083
[Otis] Straight, straight. I got you.

59:03.833 --> 59:05.166
[Vinh in Vietnamese]

59:07.208 --> 59:09.708
["What's Happening Brother"
by Marvin Gaye playing]

59:09.791 --> 59:12.958
♪ Hey, baby, whatcha know good ♪

59:14.583 --> 59:17.458
♪ I'm just gettin' back
But you knew I would ♪

59:17.541 --> 59:18.375
Yeah!

59:18.833 --> 59:20.916
-♪ War is hell ♪
-Ha!

59:21.000 --> 59:23.000
♪ When will it end? ♪

59:24.000 --> 59:28.625
♪ When will people start
Gettin' together again? ♪

59:29.541 --> 59:33.041
♪ Are things really getting better ♪

59:33.125 --> 59:37.416
♪ Like the newspaper said? ♪

59:39.000 --> 59:41.250
♪ Tell me what's happening, brother ♪

59:41.333 --> 59:43.333
♪ I don't know what's happening ♪

59:44.208 --> 59:46.958
♪ What's happening?
What's happening, brother? ♪

59:47.041 --> 59:48.791
♪ What's happening, brother? ♪

59:48.875 --> 59:49.875
♪ What's happening? ♪

59:49.958 --> 59:51.291
♪ What's happening, brother? ♪

59:54.666 --> 59:57.083
♪ What's happening, brother? ♪

59:57.958 --> 59:59.208
♪ What's happening, my man? ♪

59:59.291 --> 1:00:01.791
-What's happening, my man?
-What's happening, my man?

1:00:04.208 --> 1:00:05.375
How you holding up?

1:00:06.416 --> 1:00:08.416
Boy, you ask me that every five minutes.

1:00:08.500 --> 1:00:11.833
You know, I did make it through Nam
on my own. Typical tours, too.

1:00:11.916 --> 1:00:14.791
-[chuckles]
-Hey! Hey, hold up.

1:00:15.416 --> 1:00:17.000
Let Otis catch up.

1:00:17.083 --> 1:00:19.250
Damn, Paul, you can still
hump it out on point.

1:00:19.333 --> 1:00:20.166
[Paul] Oh, yeah, baby.

1:00:20.250 --> 1:00:21.750
What happens if somebody get heatstroke

1:00:21.833 --> 1:00:23.458
or sprain an ankle or something?

1:00:23.791 --> 1:00:26.291
Otis is a medic. A good one, too.

1:00:26.375 --> 1:00:28.166
Even took a few rounds out of me once.

1:00:28.250 --> 1:00:30.458
From your black monkey ass, as I recall.

1:00:30.541 --> 1:00:32.041
[all laughing]

1:00:33.958 --> 1:00:34.791
What's that?

1:00:35.791 --> 1:00:36.750
Water.

1:00:37.708 --> 1:00:40.416
What? I need to take a breathalyzer test?

1:00:41.791 --> 1:00:44.875
-Well, what are those?
-[Otis] It's something for my hip.

1:00:44.958 --> 1:00:46.625
I know that. But what are they?

1:00:47.791 --> 1:00:48.625
OxyContin.

1:00:49.208 --> 1:00:51.208
[laughs] Are you fuckin' kiddin' me?

1:00:51.291 --> 1:00:54.416
You think I'm sneakin' a drink,
and you on that opioid epidemic shit.

1:00:54.500 --> 1:00:57.166
